<?xml version="1.0"?>
<package xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <metadata>
    <id>calibre</id>
    <title>Calibre</title>
    <version>0.8.63</version>
    <authors>Kovid Goyal</authors>
    <owners>Gary Ewan Park</owners>
    <summary>calibre is the one stop solution to all your e-book needs.</summary>
    <description>calibre is a free and open source e-book library management application developed by users of e-books for users of e-books.</description>
    <projectUrl>http://calibre-ebook.com/</projectUrl>
    <tags>ebook library management</tags>
    <copyright>Kovid Goyal</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.ico</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: E-book viewer: Allow quick saving and loading of viewer settings as 'themes'.    
    - New: Ebook-viewer: Add a restore defaults button to the viewer preferences dialog
    - New: E-book viewer: Add simple settings for text and background colors
    - New: Add an entry to save to disk when right clicking a format in the book details panel
    - New: ODT metadata: Read first image as the metadata cover from ODT files. Also allow ODT authors to set custom properties for extended metadata.
    - New: E-book viewer and PDF Output: Resize images that are longer than the page to fit onto a single page
    - Fixed: KF8 Output: Fix bug where some calibre generated KF8 files would cause the Amazon KF8 viewer on the Touch to go to into an infinite loop when using the next page function
    - Fixed: News download: Add support for <img> tags that link to SVG images.
    - Fixed: Update podofo to 0.9.1 in all binary builds, to fix corruption of some PDFs when updating metadata.
    - Fixed: Catalog generation: Handle authors whose last name is a number.
    - Fixed: KF8 Input: Handle html entities in the NCX toc entries correctly
    - Fixed: Fix a calibre crash that affected some windows installs
    - Fixed: MOBI Output: Normalize unicode strings before writing to file, to workaround lack of support for non-normal unicode in Amazon's MOBI renderer.
    - Fixed: EPUB Input: Handle files that have duplicate entries in the spine
    - Fixed: Fix regression in Kobo driver that caused the on device column to not be updated after deleting books
    - New News Source: Dziennik Polski by Gregorz Maj
    - New News Source: High Country Blogs by Armin Geller
    - New News Source: Philosophy Now by Rick Shang
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
